2 (3) The utility consumer participation board is created within
3 in the department and shall exercise its powers and duties under
4 this act independently of the department. The procurement and
5 related management functions of the board shall must be performed
6 under the direction and supervision of the department. The board
7 shall consist consists of 5 members appointed by the governor, 1 of
8 whom shall must be chosen from 1 or more lists of qualified persons
9 submitted by the attorney general.
10 (4) For the purposes of subsection (5) only, "utility" means
11 an electric or gas company located in or outside of this state.
