19 a term, the member shall must be appointed for the balance of the
20 unexpired term of the member to be succeeded.
21 (7) The governor shall remove a member of the board if that
22 member is absent for any reason from either 3 consecutive board
23 meetings or more than 50% of the meetings held by the board in a
24 calendar year. However, an individual who is removed due to
25 absenteeism is eligible for reappointment to fill a vacancy that
26 occurs in the board membership. The governor also shall remove a
27 member of the board if the member is subsequently determined to be
