10 Midcontinent Independent System Operator or the applicable regional
11 transmission organization. As used in this sub-subparagraph, "firm
12 capacity" means capacity that is accredited to meet the utility's
13 planning reserve margin requirement during periods of highest loss
14 of load risk.
15 (B) For a resource that is not a dispatchable resource
16 described in sub-subparagraph (A), the commission shall add the
17 associated integration costs required to maintain system
18 reliability. The commission shall calculate associated integration
19 costs based on the cost of new entry for a comparable firm,
20 dispatchable resource required to provide equivalent reliability
21 services. As used in this sub-subparagraph, "associated integration
22 costs" includes, but is not limited to, the cost of firming
23 capacity, transmission upgrades, and ancillary services required to
