21 documents.
22 (ii) Allows all contractors and subcontractors on the
23 construction project to compete for contracts and subcontracts
24 without regard to whether they are otherwise parties to collective
25 bargaining agreements.
26 (iii) Contains guarantees against strikes, lockouts, and similar
27 job disruptions.
28 (iv) Sets forth effective, prompt, and mutually binding
29 procedures for resolving labor disputes arising during the term of
KHS H02431'25 a (H-1) 8jyogi

43
1 the project labor agreement.
2 (v) Provides other mechanisms for labor-management cooperation
3 on matters of mutual interest and concern, including productivity,
4 quality of work, safety, and health.
5 (vi) Complies with all state and federal laws, rules, and
6 regulations.
7 (c) (d) The plan is consistent with the renewable energy plan
